The chip is a microcontroller.  It needs a program called &quot;firmware&quot; put 
into it before it will do anything useful.  The chips have a program 
memory which comes blank when you buy them.

The &quot;code&quot; is the representation of what is called machine language 
that tells the various parts of the microcontroller what to do.  In this 
case, I imagine it increases a voltage with a certain pattern and then 
drops it down to zero, starting over again and repeating at a certain 
rate. This would produce a repetitive sweep of the radio at a certain rate 
when the microcontroller is hooked up to the radio correctly.

It wouldn&#39;t be difficult for me to write my own program to do this with a 
PIC microcontroller, but if someone else has already done it, why bother?

If I can&#39;t get my hands on the machine code, I&#39;ll write some myself.

Zack

